<TEXT>
<P>
A Rancho Palos Verdes man who allegedly fired his gun into a carload of 
teen-agers on a scavenger hunt, injuring a 16-year-old boy, has been charged 
with assault with a deadly weapon and shooting into an inhabited vehicle. 
</P>
<P>
Carl Faulkner, 43, faces up to 13 years in prison, if he is convicted of the 
two felony charges filed Tuesday in South Bay Municipal Court. 
</P>
<P>
