students might be charged with trespassing, but the district attorney's office 
has declined to prosecute. The youths were not trespassing because Poe's car 
was parked in the street and their tampering with the license plate was so 
minor that it does not warrant filing criminal charges, said Deputy Dist. Atty. 
Martin Oghigian. 
</P>
